new property task for scheduled_job decorator

Adding this simple property we can easily access APScheduler's scheduled_job decorator.
So in Flask we could create a scheduler file and write our schedule as so:

@scheduler.task("cron", id="test_print_hello", minute="*")
def print_hello():
    print("Hello as Cron")

or 

@scheduler.task("interval", id="test_print_hello", seconds=120, misfire_grace_time=900)
def print_hello():
    print("Hello as Interval")

See: https://apscheduler.readthedocs.io/en/latest/modules/triggers/cron.html

commit.message:
Fix Typo of `JobLookupError`

The [LookupError](https://docs.python.org/2/library/exceptions.html#exceptions.LookupError) is python base exception for errors like `IndexError`, `KeyError`, etc. It will generate a message like `Job xxx not found` if the job func throw an `IndexError` or `KeyError`.

The [LookupError](https://docs.python.org/2/library/exceptions.html#exceptions.LookupError) is python base exception for errors like `IndexError`, `KeyError`, etc. It will generate a message like `Job xxx not found` if the job func throw an `IndexError` or `KeyError`.
